Version: 0.1.04.11 (virgo)

Description: GmailCommandLine is a simple app to send e-mail by a  gmail account. It was build in order to send fast e-mail no be necessary open your gmail account in browser.


Uage: gmailcommandline.py [options]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -d DESTINATION, --destination=DESTINATION
                        set a destination address to send e-mail, else send to
                        default: yourself mail
  -a ATTACH, --attachpath=ATTACH
                        Attach  a file to email.
  -m "MESSAGE", --message="MESSAGE"
                        The message that you want to send.
  -u USERMAIL, --usermail=USERMAIL
                        Here put you user email of Gmail.        Just need set
                        in the first time that use this  program.
  -s SUBJECT, --subject=SUBJECT
                         The subject of email.

Example: python gmailcommanline.py -u greg@gmail.com -s Teste -m "Hello World!!" -d jonhdoo@anymailserver.com -a /home/greg/imagens/partytoday.png

